Time Model Statistics

  • DB Time represents total time in user calls
  • DB CPU represents CPU time of foreground processes
  • Total CPU Time represents foreground and background processes
  • Statistics including the word "background" measure background process time, therefore do not contribute to the DB time statistic
  • Ordered by % of DB time in descending order, followed by Statistic Name

1af44tbprtczjMERGE INTO VTIMPCARD CRD USING ( SELECT SUM(PTRN.CARDBALAMT) AS CARDBALAMT, SUM(PTRN.CASHBAKAMT) AS CASHBAKAMT, SUM(PTRN.TRNAMT) AS TRNAMT, PTRN.PCARDID FROM VTPTPOSTRNREQ ORGTRN INNER JOIN VTPTTRNREQ PTRN ON PTRN.POSTRNREQID = ORGTRN.POSTRNREQID WHERE ORGTRN.POSCLIENTID=:B2 AND ORGTRN.TRNREQTYPE='SALE' AND ORGTRN.POSBATCHID = :B1 AND ORGTRN.CURRSTATUSCODE = '85' AND ORGTRN.MODEPAY='04' AND ORGTRN.VOIDREVFLAG='N' GROUP BY PTRN.PCARDID ) TRN ON (CRD.PCARDID = TRN.PCARDID) WHEN MATCHED THEN UPDATE SET CRD.CARDBAL=CRD.CARDBAL+ NVL(TRN.CARDBALAMT, 0) , CRD.CASHBAKBAL= CRD.CASHBAKBAL + NVL(TRN.CASHBAKAMT, 0), CRD.TOTCARDBAL= CRD.TOTCARDBAL+ TRN.TRNAMT
1fypbsku5w5uvMERGE INTO VTIMPTRNAMT T USING ( SELECT NVL(SUM(PTRN.TRNAMT - NVL(PTRN.ADHOCAMTUSED, 0)), 0) AS TRNAMT, PTRN.PCARDID FROM VTPTPOSTRNREQ ORGTRN INNER JOIN VTPTTRNREQ PTRN ON PTRN.POSTRNREQID = ORGTRN.POSTRNREQID WHERE ORGTRN.POSCLIENTID=:B2 AND ORGTRN.TRNREQTYPE='SALE' AND ORGTRN.POSBATCHID = :B1 AND ORGTRN.CURRSTATUSCODE='85' AND ORGTRN.MODEPAY='06' AND ORGTRN.VOIDREVFLAG='N' GROUP BY PTRN.PCARDID ) TRN ON ( T.PCARDID = TRN.PCARDID ) WHEN MATCHED THEN UPDATE SET FO_DLY_TRNAMT = FO_DLY_TRNAMT - TRN.TRNAMT, FO_MNTH_TRNAMT = FO_MNTH_TRNAMT - TRN.TRNAMT, FO_CMSP_DLY_TRN = FO_CMSP_DLY_TRN - TRN.TRNAMT, FO_CMSP_MNTH_TRN=FO_CMSP_MNTH_TRN-TRN.TRNAMT WHERE T.FO_DLY_TRNAMT IS NOT NULL

NVL(LD.ADHOCAMTUSED, :"SYS_B_15")) , CD.PCARDID FROM VTIMPCARD CD INNER JOIN VTLTLOADTRN LD ON (LD.PCARDID = CD.PCARDID) INNER JOIN VTPTPOSTRNREQ TRN ON TRN.POSTRNREQID = LD.POSTRNREQID WHERE CD.CUSTID=:2 AND TRN.TRNREQDATE > TO_DATE(TO_CHAR(SYSDATE-:"SYS_B_16", :"SYS_B _17") || :"SYS_B_18", :"SYS_B_19") AND TRN.CURRSTATUSCODE = :"SYS_B_20" AND TRN.TRNREQTYPE = :"SYS_B_21" GROUP BY CD.PCARDID ) GROUP BY PCARDID ) DLMT ON DLMT.PCARDID = CRD.PCARDID LEFT JOIN (SELECT SUM(MAMT) AS MAMT , PCARDID FROM (SELECT NVL(SUM( CASE WHEN CD.LIMITTYPE = :"SYS_B_22" THEN NVL(TRN.TRNAMT , :"SYS_B_23") - SUM(NVL(LD.ADHOCAMTUSED, :"SYS_B_34")) MAMT , CD.PCARDID FROM VTIMPCARD CD INNER JOIN VTLTLOADTRN LD ON (LD.PCARDID = CD.PCARDID) INNER JOIN VTPTPOSTRNREQ TRN ON (TRN.POSTRNREQID = LD.POSTRNREQID) WHERE CD.CUSTID= :4 AND TRN.TRNREQDATE > TO_DATE(TO_CHAR(LAST_DAY(ADD_MONTHS(SYSDATE, -:"SYS_B_35")), :"SYS_B_36") ||:"SYS_B_37", :"SYS_B_38") AND TRN.CURRSTATUSCODE = :"SYS_B_39" AND TRN.TRNREQTYPE = :"SYS_B_40" GROUP BY CD.PCARDID ) GROUP BY PCARDID ) MLMT ON MLMT.PCARDID = CRD.PCARDID LEFT JOIN VTCMPERSN PERS ON PERS.CUSTCHLDID = CRD.CUSTCHLDID LEFT JOIN VTCMVEHICLE VEH ON VEH.VEHICLEID = CRD.VEHICLEID WHERE CRD.CUSTID = :5 AND CRD.CURRSTATUS < :"SYS_B_41"

Back to Top

Undo Segment Summary

  • Min/Max TR (mins) - Min and Max Tuned Retention (minutes)
  • STO - Snapshot Too Old count, OOS - Out of Space count
  • Undo segment block stats:
  • uS - unexpired Stolen, uR - unexpired Released, uU - unexpired reUsed
  • eS - expired Stolen, eR - expired Released, eU - expired reUsed

Impact is 10.8 active sessions, 1.51% of total activity.
--------------------------------------------------------

   Recommendation 1: Host Configuration
   Estimated benefit is 10.8 active sessions, 1.51% of total activity.
   -------------------------------------------------------------------
   Action
      Consider increasing the throughput of the I/O subsystem. Oracle's
      recommended solution is to stripe all data files using the SAME
      methodology. You might also need to increase the number of disks for
      better performance.
   Rationale
      During the analysis period, the average data files' I/O throughput was
      2290 M per second for reads and 2.1 M per second for writes. The average
      response time for single block reads was 10 milliseconds.

   Estimated benefit is 10.8 active sessions, 1.51% of total activity.
   -------------------------------------------------------------------
   Action
      The performance of some data and temp files was significantly worse than
      others. If striping all files using the SAME methodology is not
      possible, consider striping these file over multiple disks.

Finding 4: CPU Usage
Impact is 51.36 active sessions, 10.91% of total activity.
----------------------------------------------------------
Host CPU was a bottleneck and the instance was consuming 79% of the host CPU.
All wait times will be inflated by wait for CPU.
Host CPU consumption was 79%.

   Recommendation 1: Host Configuration
   Estimated benefit is 51.41 active sessions, 10.91% of total activity.
   ---------------------------------------------------------------------
   Action
      Consider adding more CPUs to the host or adding instances serving the
      database on other hosts.
   Action
      Also consider using Oracle Database Resource Manager to prioritize the
      workload from various consumer groups.

  • target instances.

  • Average and standard deviation of ping latency is given in miliseconds

  • Note that latency of a message from the instance to itself is used as
  • control, since message latency can include wait for CPU
